TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Core of an N Person Game
AU  - Scarf, Herbert E.
AB  - [Sufficient conditions are given for a general n person game to have a nonempty core. The conditions are a consequence of convexity of preferences if the game arises from an exchange economy. The proof of sufficiency is based on a finite algorithm, and makes no use of fixed point theorems.]
